05716nam a22008415i 9783110939743DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20111996gw     fo  d z      ger d  a97831109397437 a10.1515/97831109397432doi  a(DE-B1597)44763  a(OCoLC)979607216  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 ager  agwcDE 4aBR854b.I58 1994eb 7aLIT0000002bisacsh04a274.3/03221  aGE 86032rvk0(DE-625)rvk/39339:04aDie Vermittlung geistlicher Inhalte im deutschen Mittelalter :bInternationales Symposium, Roscrea 1994 /chrsg. von Timothy R. Jackson, Nigel F. Palmer, Almut Suerbaum.  aReprint 2011 1aTübingen : bMax Niemeyer Verlag, c[2011] 4c©1996  a1 online resource (337 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aSchwerpunkte dieses aus einer 1994 in Roscrea (Irland) veranstalteten Tagung hervorgehenden Bandes sind insbesondere: Mariendichtung, Chronistik, handschriftliche Überlieferung und Illustration, Editionstechnik. Weiter kommen jiddische Bibelübersetzungen, das geistliche Spiel und unterschiedliche Formen der Heiligenverehrung ins Gespräch. Dabei werden neben namhaften Autoren wie Mechthild von Magdeburg, Der Stricker und Priester Wernher auch weniger bekannte wie Wilhelm Müncher (Pfaffe in Engelmairszell bei Pfaffenhausen an der Ilm) behandelt. Die Sammlung bringt ferner eine Edition des Textes „Von der seligen Schererin“ (frühes 15. Jahrhundert), die über die von einer verheirateten Frau im familiären Rahmen erlebten Auditionen und Visionen berichtet.  aThis volume is the fruit of a symposium held in Roscrea (Ireland) in 1994 and concentrates on literature in praise of the Virgin Mary, chronicles, manuscripts, illustration and editing procedures. Also dealt with are Yiddish Bible translations, religious plays and various literary forms of veneration of the saints. The authors referred to range from famous names such as Mechthild von Magdeburg, Der Stricker and Priester Wernher to less familiar figures like Wilhelm Münchner (cleric in Engelmairszell near Pfaffenhausen on the Ilm). The collection also includes an edition of the text "Von der seligen Schererin" (early 15th century), which relates the visions and aural visitations experienced by a married woman in her normal family surroundings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aFlood, John L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGutfleisch-Ziche, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGärtner, Kurt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHellgardt, Ernst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenkel, Nikolaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Timothy R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKurmann, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLutz, Eckart Conrad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacardle, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiedema, Nine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrtmann, Christa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPalmer, Nigel F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRagotzky, Hedda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRöll, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchiewer, Hans-Jochen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShaw, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSherwood-Smith, Ma